        {
          "text": "In the general discussion channel, community members raised several topics. A user requested an unban for someone named arisae, to which a moderator responded that no one by that name appeared to be banned. Another user asked about the release of V3, noting that Shaw had previously indicated it would arrive soon, though no confirmed release date was provided. Separately, a discussion emerged around a reported partnership between the Secure Blockchain Development Corp and the Eliza Foundation, aimed at commercializing an Agentic SME solution using the ElizaOS framework. One user described it as a Canadian listed entity deal with a 30-day timeline for a v1 and approximately 90 days for full deployment. Another user expressed skepticism, suggesting nothing had been formally signed, which prompted a rebuttal defending the legitimacy and outlined timeline of the partnership. In the coders channel, activity was minimal with only a casual greeting posted.",
